College degree preferred, but not required. We appreciate solid work experience;
5+ years of experience in Full Stack/web development experience;
Familiarity with jQuery and PHP;
Experience building customer facing applications;
Strong Javascript experience with deep expertise in at least one of the leading Javascript frameworks – React, Angular, Vue;
Familiarity with jQuery;
Experience with JS unit testing and test libraries;
Experience with and front-end tooling such as Webpack, Gulp, or similar;
RESTful API development experience in Java, .NET or node.js;
Experience with SQL in backend database;
Strong analytical, problem-solving, and decision-making skills;
Strong sense of web design and attuned to the fundamentals of user experience;
You have been intimately involved with optimizing delivery of web-based applications;
Familiarity with the whole web stack, including protocols and web server optimization techniques;
Experience with AWS technologies, desired;
Strong communication skills; and
Work authorization: United States (Required).
